	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Verant tries to change history?</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=532005" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
A short while ago, I recieved an e-mail from a user who insisted to point out how I was wrong, and verant has been saying for two months that DirectX 8.1 would be required.  The user even sent me a URL to EQ's official forum posted on 10-11:<br><br>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000348.html">Click Here</a><br><br>

After going to the URL, I was shocked!  It appeared the user was right, and Verant did tell everyone 2 months ago that DirectX 8.1 would be required!  If this was the case, then I owed everyone on lore a public appology for some of the statements that I made in regards to Verant keeping the change to DX 8.1 a secret!<br><br>

Nearly certain that I had seen that same article only a few days before showing 8.0a, I did a little further digging around, I found two additional links, from two other fan sites that had cut and copied that article from the official forum the day it was posted :

<a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3840">http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3840</a> from CastersRealm.com and <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/archive/arc4.shtml">http://eqvault.ign.com/archive/arc4.shtml</a> from EQVault.  Surprisingly, both show the article as saying 8.0a instead of 8.1.<br><br>

Is it possible that Both CastersRealm and EQVault are involved in a conspiricy to make Verant look bad, or are we seeing someone at Verant going back and trying to alter history to make it appear that Verant has been saying DirectX 8.1 for the last 2 months, and no one was listening?<br><br>

Two other messages of interest that I have found on the official EQ forums were <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000394.html">HERE</a> which still has DX 8.0 or better as the requirments on 11-26, and <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000401.html">HERE</a> Where on 12-03, 1 day before the patch, Absor still denied that EQ would be switching to requiring DX 8.1.  It was not until <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000407.html">HERE</a> on 12-04, the day of the patch that it was verified that 8.1 would be needed.  <i>(note: the info mentioned about these posts is accurate at the time of this article, and can not account for any future "modifications" that verant may make to the listed posts)</i>
<blockquote><i>
<b>Note To Readers</b> : Although it may appear that we have been doing some Verant bashing the last few days, in reporting the problems that we have found.  Please understand it is not because we hate the game, in fact we very much love the game, and would not run a site like this if we did not.  Instead, as a news site, it is our job to keep players advised of both the good and bad news.  Although you personally may not be directly effected by these issues, we hope that our readers will keep in mind that other players are.  We also strongly believe that the only way by which to make a great game even better is to identify potential errors in judgement on the part of senior administrators so that such errors may be avoided in the future.
</i></blockquote>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
